{"word":"H6470 - פָּעַם - pâʻam - paw-am' - Move","slug":"H6470","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּעַם</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pâʻam"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-am'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Move"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05E2;&#x05DD; - pa&#x0302;&#x201B;am</b> - <i>paw-am'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>tap</i>, that is, beat regularly; hence (generally) to <i>impel</i> or <i>agitate: - </i>move, trouble."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H6471\">H6471</a>, <a href=\"#/H6472\">H6472</a>"}]}